text: Eline Timmerman (born 30 December 1998) is a Dutch volleyball player who plays as a middle blocker. Timmerman started playing volleyball at Rivo Rijssen. Between 2014 and 2016 she played with the Talent Team Papendal. From 2016 to 2018 she played with Alterno in Apeldoorn. Afterwards she played with Team Eurosped in Vroomshoop for two years. Since 2020 she plays with in Germany with Ladies in Black Aachen. She is member of the Netherlands women's national volleybal team. She made her debut in 2019 during the 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's Nations League. She competed at the 2022 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch volleyball players Category:Sportspeople from Overijssel Category:Sportswomen
